\b0 \cf0 The authors give a good example of how one of the provisions could be used to either increase or decrease shareholder rights, based on the boards desires. \
Take Classified Boards for example. This describes how the terms and elections of directors can be staggered and hence be used to slow down a hostile takeover. Management could use this to lead to an increase or decrease in overall shareholder wealth, depending on how this power is handled. \
Since board turnover is more gradual, it is more difficult for a hostile company to gain control and take over.\
Other provisions can be thought of in a similar way, in that they can be used to either increase or hamper shareholders activism (calling special meetings, changing the firms bylaws etc). 
